lead_paragraph: Though she lost in the second round of the Australian Open, Bouchard is ahead of where she thought she would be after a concussion put her out of last year’s United States Open.

headline.print_headline: Bouchard, on Comeback Trail, Skids a Bit Against Radwanska
headline.main: Eugenie Bouchard Exits Knowing a Full Comeback Will Take Time

snippet: Though she lost in the second round of the Australian Open, Bouchard is ahead of where she thought she would be after a concussion put her out of last year’s United States Open.
abstract: Eugenie Bouchard, despite second-round loss at Australian Open tennis tournament, is surprising many with her dominant return since sustaining concussion in September 2015; has already won seven matches in first two weeks of 2016.
